        # Supporting document for underwater slot

        Work Hard! Play Hard! test test test


        ## Background

        Dear [\$ownerPreferredName\$]{.shiny},

        We are very glad that you decided to spend this time together, flooded with unexpected nets and a flickering co-presence.

        So, you have become part of the annual Work Hard! Play Hard! event it is self-organized and what happens inside of the week depends on those who participate in it. This year, WHPH is being held for the fifth time. Usually, everyone stays at friends' apartments, events take place in various friendly venues, on the streets of the city, in unexpected secret places. As a rule, everyone moves together in Minsk, after that they spend time in a sanatorium, living there or coming to attend events. This year, the pandemic deformed calendars and spaces, closed borders, but the working group decided to hold an event, synthesizing the possibilities of new connections remotely and distributed.

        an underwater slot  is an attempt to  to reveal the synthesis of affect, to make sensual adventure accomplices out of us, floating in the computational waters, a distributed care cooperative.

        Proposed roles thematise the space between events in the schedule grid. They happen somewhere between the lines when you glance at [the color fill of the website](http://workhardplay.pw/en/2020/index.html). They are a hidden engine of events, the fragile infrastructure that tingles the skin with hot sprays

        Do not tell anyone about your  role  practice of caring  mission  underwater character neither now nor during the week.

        How much you want to get it alive / activate / fit in / dive is up to you. What experience you have will depend entirely on your willingness to get involved, act, respond.

        Get ready to dive into the intimate infrastructure of WHPH, into  UNDERWATER  ROLES  CARE PRACTICES  MISSIONS , which will accompany us for one week

        Have a nice swim! ➟   ➟   ➟ ➟   ➟   ➟ ➟   ➟   ➟

        ## Game features

        This game is a mixture of art and gaming techniques, written larps, online role-playing games and freewheeling of participants.

        A feature of these techniques is a small presence of rules, greater freedom of action of the players and an open finale. Only you know where the game can lead you (sometimes, even you cannot predict this ). There are no spectators in this game – everyone becomes its direct participants.


        ## Your underwater role / practice of care / mission

        So, you have already identified the role or roles that you claimed and were able to develop them a bit in the process of filling out the form underwater slot.

        Before the game, we ask you to take 30 minutes to work on your character, whether it’s "you yourself" or you with a shifted identity, your underwater creature.

        To do this, you can take a piece of paper and write-draw-render-make-alive the answers to the following questions. You can also go beyond and add the questions if it seems to you that your character requires it. Fiddle with your identity

        ## QUESTIONS FOR WORKING INDIVIDUALLY ON YOUR CHARACTER:

        Start exploring your role with a memory of what water you like to be in – cold, hot, whitewater, icy? And what about your underwater entity?

        Next continue answering the questions as your character:

        How do you usually feel in groups of people? Are you comfortable being physically close to other people? And virtually?

        Do you often need support nearby to communicate, or do you yourself at times provide such support to people close to you?

        What kind of support could you give to another person who needs you?

        Do you like typing fast on your keyboard?

        How do you feel about virtual communication tools? Did you manage to collar them? If not, what or who is stopping you?

        Has your underwater creature already visited WHPH before? If so, remember what was the most valuable experience for you there. If not, would you like to go next year? What experience do you want to find there?

        Where did you wake up this morning?

        How do you feel about your underwater partners? Why do you need her/him/them?

